bayu: You've made it through. Bats, Frogs, the Witch's collectors — all of them.
bayu: But those were just the outer layer. Foot soldiers sent from somewhere deeper.
bayu: Every one of those creatures is being projected here through a signal — from inside the internet itself.
bayu: The gate ahead leads into Stage 2: the threshold between this world and the digital one.
bayu: Someone left a gambling app open in this city. The signal is still live — and it's pulling things through.
bayu: You have to go in. Follow the signal. Trace it back through the network to wherever it originates.
bayu: At the end of it all, there is something they call the Necromancer. The Algorithm. The House.
bayu: Every soul this city lost — every person hollowed out by debt and despair — their suffering feeds it.
bayu: The Bats and Frogs you fought today? They used to be people, just like you.
bayu: The Necromancer believes one thing above all else: the house always wins.
bayu: It has never been wrong. Until now.
bayu: Go. And whatever you do — don't play its game.
